(fifthQuint)Low Dose Ketamine for Management of Acute Severe Pain in the Emergency Department.

 Management and assessment of pain in the Emergency Department (ED) can be challenging.

 Treatment of pain is most often accomplished by parenteral opioids analgesics.

 However, inadequate analgesia is often a problem when opioids alone are relied on for pain control.

 In the peri-operative setting ketamine has been used as an adjunct to opioids for acute pain.

 Ketamine may play a role in maximizing analgesia in the ED.

